Linebackers. Gay with his lowest percentage of the season. I know he got hurt. Did he leave the game and not return, or did he come back in later? Normally my pillbox charts would tell me this... Harris with a slight uptick. Chenal barely got snaps.

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/n9tgzzXGMD

Safeties next. Pretty normal distribution here. Reid and Thornhill with basically all the snaps. Cook with an uptick as well. Wonder if that was to help counteract Gay's injury, or just a normal part of the game plan? 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/QErDBzfBSQ

On to Defense. Cornerbacks. McDuffie missed a couple snaps, apparently. Williams came back in against the team that essentially got him benched, and stepped up in a big way. All three rookies played exceptionally well. Not enough good things to say about them.

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/bpCeiwfoLi

Running backs. I am surprised this was as close as it was. Sure felt to me like Pacheco was out there most of the time. Pacheco was clearly hurting on some snaps, so I wonder if Jet had something wrong too, or if they just really liked Pacheco against Cincy. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/0rCGkmhUlj

Wide receivers next. Sorry this one got so crowded. Didn't expect both Kemp and Ihmir-Marsette to show up. Moore and Kemp both with season highs in both counts and percentages. MVS was a hero yesterday. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/5zPhFeZx5U

Tight ends first. Travis Kelce. He's the man. Gray with an uptick in snaps as well. Fortson took the normal amount of Fortson/Bell snaps.
